																		SCPs mentioned
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226079" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;" >qntm</a></span> <span class="odate time_1422665958 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Jan 2015 00:59</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2220713">
									

<p>This Tale implies the existence of several other SCPs:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-055">SCP-055</a>, a &quot;self-keeping secret&quot;. Already exists in the files; was the basis for this Tale.</li>
<li>SCP-4987: an invisible monster which follows antimemetics chief Marion Wheeler around, and likes to eat her memories. She routinely generates interesting memories for it to eat, so that it doesn't consume anything important. I like to imagine she reads and memorises trivia books, but sometimes 4987 eats genuinely important memories from her life, like her wedding anniversary. This is difficult for her to deal with.</li>
<li>(number unknown): a &quot;contagious murder&quot;. This is the death of SCP researcher Bart Hughes. He is dead, but anybody who learns exactly how he died immediately dies by precisely the same method. So, obviously the cause of death cannot be explicitly documented. In fact, the entire series of deaths (who knows how many!) has to be strenuously quarantined to prevent it from spreading.</li>
<li>(number unknown): &quot;Clay&quot;. An antimeme who apparently took on human form and posed as O5-8's assistant, for reasons not clear. Possibly he intended to find his way into the Antimemetics division and undermine or terminate the whole division?</li>
<li>And others which Wheeler knows of&#8230;</li>
<li>And others still which are nominally contained but even Wheeler doesn't know of&#8230;</li>
<li>And others which are freely roaming the halls, unchecked.</li>
</ul>
<p>I don't know whether these SCPs should actually be written up. I'm not sure if these concepts can support a full SCP - and according to the statements in this Tale, only SCP-055 should actually physically exist in the files. But maybe the state of the art advances after this Tale?</p>

							</div>

								
